T* (Proper Care and Handling) Tj
T* (- Never allow metal objects to touch the circuit board while powered.) Tj
T* (- Always handle the board with proper anti-static methods.) Tj
T* (- Never allow the board to directly or indirectly contact voltage spikes.) Tj
T* (- Never allow water or condensing moisture to contact the boards.) Tj
T* (- Always use caution with FPGA, firmware, or software modifications.) Tj
T* (- Never apply more than +10 dBm of power into any RF input.) Tj
T* (- Always use at least 30 dB attenuation if operating in loopback configuration.) Tj
